<!-- ─── Step 3 ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->

<div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding: 20px; background: #fff; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 6px;">
    <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #e65100;">
        <span style="display: inline-block; width: 32px; height: 32px; line-height: 32px; text-align: center; background: #e65100; color: #fff; border-radius: 50%; font-size: 16px; margin-right: 10px;">3</span>
        Configure Your .env File
    </h3>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Every Laravel application needs a <code>.env</code> file that contains its settings &mdash;
        things like database passwords, email configuration, and your app's secret key.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Go to the <strong>.env</strong> tab. If your repository has a
        <code>.env.example</code> file, it will be pre-filled for you. Update the values
        to match your server:
    </p>
    <ul style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 2;">
        <li><code>APP_URL</code> &mdash; Your full website address (e.g. <code>https://<?php echo $this->escape($this->domain->getDisplayName()); ?></code>)</li>
        <li><code>DB_DATABASE</code>, <code>DB_USERNAME</code>, <code>DB_PASSWORD</code> &mdash; Your database credentials (create a database in Plesk first under Databases)</li>
