<!-- ─── How it works under the hood ──────────────────────── -->

<div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding: 20px; background: #f5f5f5; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 6px;">
    <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">How Zero-Downtime Deploys Work</h3>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Traditional deployment replaces your files while the site is running, which can cause errors
        if a visitor loads a page mid-update. XVE Laravel Kit uses a different approach:
    </p>
    <div style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; background: #fff; border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 4px; padding: 16px; margin: 16px 0; line-height: 1.8;">
        <?php echo $this->escape($this->domain->getDisplayName()); ?>/<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;releases/<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20250309_143000/&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: #888;">&larr; deploy from March 9</span><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20250310_091500/&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: #888;">&larr; deploy from March 10</span><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20250311_160000/&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: #888;">&larr; latest deploy (March 11)</span><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;shared/<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.env&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: #888;">&larr; your settings (shared across all versions)</span><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;storage/&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: #888;">&larr; uploads, logs, cache (shared)</span><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;current/ &rarr; releases/20250311_160000/&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: #2e7d32; font-weight: bold;">&larr; this is what visitors see</span>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Each deploy creates a new folder under <code>releases/</code>.
        The <code>current/</code> pointer tells the web server which version to show.
        Switching versions is instant because it just changes where <code>current/</code> points to.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0;">
        Your <code>.env</code> file and <code>storage/</code> folder (uploads, logs) live in the
        <code>shared/</code> directory. They're linked into each release so your data is always
        available, no matter which version is active. Old releases are kept for rollback
        (the number is configurable in Settings).
    </p>
</div>

<!-- ─── Troubleshooting ──────────────────────────────────── -->

<div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding: 20px; background: #fce4ec; border: 1px solid #ef9a9a; border-radius: 6px;">
    <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #c62828;">Troubleshooting</h3>

    <h4 style="margin-bottom: 4px;">Deploy fails with "Permission denied (publickey)"</h4>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        The deploy key hasn't been added to your repository, or it was added incorrectly.
        Go to <strong>Settings</strong>, copy the SSH Public Key, and add it to your repository's
        deploy keys. Make sure you copy the entire key (it starts with <code>ssh-ed25519</code>).
    </p>

    <h4 style="margin-bottom: 4px;">Site shows a blank page or 500 error after deploy</h4>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Check the <strong>.env</strong> tab &mdash; make sure all required settings are filled in
        (especially <code>APP_KEY</code>, database credentials, and <code>APP_URL</code>).
        Then check the <strong>Log</strong> tab for specific error messages.
    </p>

    <h4 style="margin-bottom: 4px;">Deploy fails with "composer: command not found"</h4>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Composer needs to be installed on the server. In Plesk, go to
        <strong>Tools & Settings</strong> and make sure PHP Composer is available.
    </p>

    <h4 style="margin-bottom: 4px;">Changes to .env don't take effect</h4>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0;">
        Laravel caches its configuration for performance. After changing the <code>.env</code> file,
        go to the <strong>Artisan</strong> tab and run <code>config:clear</code>, or tick the
        "Cache config after saving" checkbox when editing the .env file.
    </p>
</div>
